Wash and dry produce.

Pat @Fully Cooked Chicken Breasts{8.6%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Thinly
slice crosswise into strips.

In a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine chicken, @Turkish Spice Blend{1%tbsp},
a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}, a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cover with
#plastic wrap{} and microwave until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and quarter @Mini Cucumber{1} lengthwise; halve crosswise. Cut
@Tomato{1} into ½-inch wedges; season with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and @salt{}.

Wrap @Flour Tortillas{2} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until soft and
pliable, ~{20-30%seconds}.

Lay tortillas out on a clean work surface. Spread @Hummus{1/2%cup} over bottom
half of each tortilla; top with spiced chicken (draining first), cucumber, and
seasoned tomato. Fold up bottom side of each tortilla over filling, then fold
over left and right sides toward the filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with
filled sides, to form wraps.

Halve wraps on a diagonal; divide between plates and serve.